<img class=" wp-image-1424047 aligncenter" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/courts.png?resize=554%2C369&#038;ssl=1" alt="Mobile Court convicts 33 persons for violation of COVID-19 protocols" width="554" height="369" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/courts.png?resize=300%2C200&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/courts.png?resize=58%2C39&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/courts.png?resize=260%2C173&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/courts.png?resize=195%2C130&amp;ssl=1 195w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/courts.png?resize=115%2C77&amp;ssl=1 115w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/courts.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w" sizes="(max-width: 554px) 100vw, 554px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> A Kaduna Chief Magistrates’ Court on Tuesday sentenced a 25-year-old carpenter, James Gabriel, to three months’ imprisonment for buying a stolen Tecno cell phone. The convict, a resident of Sabo Tasha Kaduna, had pleaded guilty to a charge of dishonestly receiving and purchasing stolen property and begged for leniency. Magistrate Ibrahim Emmanuel sentenced him to three months’  imprisonment or an option of N5,000 fine. Earlier, the prosecutor, Insp. Chidi Leo, had told the court that Gabriel dishonestly received and purchased a stolen Tecno cell phone for N48,000. Leo said that the value of the phone, property of one Samson Pascal, was yet to be ascertained when it was recovered from the convict. The prosecutor said that in the course of a police investigation, Gabriel confessed to have committed the offence. He added that the offence contravened Section 256 of the Penal Code,  Law of Kaduna State, 2017. [NAN] Vanguard News Nigeria A 43-year-old man, Abdullahi Salisu, yesterday, appeared before a Federal High Court in Lagos over alleged 104kg tramadol trafficking. July 4, 2019 In "Crime Guard" An Ado-Ekiti Chief Magistrates’ Court, on Monday, sentenced a 39-year-old woman, Mercy Momoh, to three years imprisonment for stealing one-month-old baby. November 18, 2019 In "News" A Kaduna Chief Magistrates’ Court, on Tuesday, sentenced two brothers, Aminu Usman and Ibrahim Usman, to six months imprisonment each for stealing two plasma Television sets. Aminu, 18 and Ibrahim, 20, both residents at Kawo in Kaduna, admitted their guilt of the crime and begged the court for leniency. The… June 19, 2018 In "News"